'''pouldron''' (''plural'' pouldrons)
# A piece of [[armor]] covering the [[shoulder]] at the [[junction]] of the [[body]] piece and the [[arm]] piece.
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*'''1786''': To the [[cuirass]] were [[buckle]]d the armour for the shoulders and arms, the first called [[pouldron]]s, the second [[brassart]]s, garde bras, les avant bras, and [[corruptly]] in English, [[Vambrace]]s. &mdash; Francis Grose, ''A Treatise on Ancient Armour and Weapons'', page 22.
